column10: Mask to indicate quads that are activated at the timestamp
column14: Timing reference the relative timing mode uses. Makes use of the time reference message. Time on the reference message forms the base time for relative timing mode.See Set ref message for more info.
column18: selects the timing mode absolute/relative/immediate.Absolute runs at the specified BFN. Relative - Timestamp is relative to time reference. Immediate ignores timing and executes ASAP

column8: BFN OTA time.In absolute mode, the timestamp is the network time for the event.In relative mode , this field denotes the delta from set reference message.Immediate ignores the field
